=== Agama (Ogama) === Agama (おがま) is the location where nearly 100°C hot spring water erupts. In the past, this high-temperature water was used to boil [[:en:麻|麻]] {{ill|hemp|ja|麻|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/hemp|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to アサ}} in order to remove its bark and extract its fibers. Nowadays, it is mostly used for cooking food such as vegetables and eggs. For safety reasons—to prevent burns—tourist access to the area around Agama is prohibited. <gallery mode="Packed"> File:Nozawaonsen okama.jpg| Panoramic View of Agama File:Nozawaonsen onsentamago.jpg| Making [[:en:Onsen tamago|Onsen Egg]] at Agama </gallery> **
